<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb95dfedb-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s2605"><num value="2605">§ 2605.</num><heading> Suits to recover wrongful or fraudulent payments</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Postal Service shall request the Attorney General to bring a suit to recover with interest any payment made from moneys of, or credit granted by, the Postal Service as a result of—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb95dfedc-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s2605/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> mistake;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb95dfedd-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s2605/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> fraudulent representations;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb95dfede-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s2605/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> collusion; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb95dfedf-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s2605/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> misconduct of an officer or employee of the Postal Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb95dfee0-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/745">84 Stat. 745</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb95dfee1-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb95dfee2-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb95dfee3-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1971-07-01">July 1, 1971</date>, pursuant to Resolution No. 71–9 of the Board of Governors. See <ref href="/us/pl/91/375/s15/a">section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, set out as a note preceding <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
